{{Infobox medical condition (new) | name = {{PAGENAME}} | synonyms = Hydrocephalus-endocardial fibroelastosis-cataract syndrome | image = | alt = | caption = | pronounce = | field = | symptoms = | complications = | onset = | duration = | types = | causes = | risks = | diagnosis = | differential = | prevention = | treatment = | medication = | prognosis = | frequency = | deaths = }} '''HEC syndrome''' is a syndrome characterized by [[hydrocephalus]], [[endocardial fibroelastosis]] and [[cataract]]s.<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Devi A, Eisenfeld L, Uphoff D, Greenstein R | title=New syndrome of hydrocephalus, endocardial fibroelastosis, and cataracts (HEC syndrome). | journal=Am J Med Genet | volume=56 | issue=1 | pages=62–6 | year=1995 | pmid=7747788 | doi=10.1002/ajmg.1320560114}}</ref>
